The paper discusses the performance of the Langevin algorithm in the context of noisy high-dimensional inference, which is a topic related to information theory (cs.IT), machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), and neural networks (cs.NE). The paper also mentions the spiked matrix-tensor model, which is a topic related to statistical inference (cs.SI). Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.IT, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.SI, and cs.NE, in that order.
